Create Artificial Comments Column

In[9]:
# --- Sample Comments ---
sample_comments = [
    "The teacher explained very clearly!",
    "Presentation was boring.",
    "Loved the session, very helpful.",
    "Too fast, couldn't understand much.",
    "Great course content!",
    "Average teaching style.",
    "Well structured and interactive session."
]

# --- Repeat comments to match dataframe length ---
sample_comments_extended = (
    sample_comments * (len(df_5) // len(sample_comments) + 1)
)[:len(df_5)]

# --- Add to dataframe ---
df_5["Comments"] = sample_comments_extended

# --- Check ---

Apply Sentiment Analysis

In[10]:
def get_sentiment(text):
    return TextBlob(text).sentiment.polarity

df_5["Sentiment"] = df_5["Comments"].apply(get_sentiment)

def label_sentiment(value):
    if value > 0.1:
        return "Positive"
    elif value < -0.1:
        return "Negative"
    else:
        return "Neutral"

df_5["Sentiment_Label"] = df_5["Sentiment"].apply(label_sentiment)
df_5.head()

Rating vs Difficulty Heatmap

In[12]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Difficulty column
difficulty_col = 'Degree of difficulty of assignments'

# Rating columns (all except ID + difficulty)
rating_cols = [
    'Well versed with the subject',
    'Explains concepts in an understandable way',
    'Use of presentations',
    'Solves doubts willingly',
    'Structuring of the course',
    'Provides support for students going above and beyond',
    'Course recommendation based on relevance'
]

# Group by difficulty & take mean of all ratings
heatmap_data = df.groupby(difficulty_col)[rating_cols].mean()

# Plot beautiful heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.heatmap(
    heatmap_data,
    annot=True,
    fmt=".2f",
    cmap='coolwarm',
    linewidths=1,
    linecolor='white'
)

plt.title("Rating vs Difficulty Heatmap", fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
plt.xlabel("Rating Factors", fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel("Difficulty Level", fontsize=12)
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.yticks(rotation=0)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Final Insights Summary

The student feedback analysis indicates an overall positively inclined learning experience, with most responses showing consistency across evaluation parameters.

Average ratings cluster between 3 and 4, suggesting stable satisfaction and a generally effective teaching approach.

Strong correlations emerge:

Clear explanations stronger understanding

Well-structured content higher relevance

Supportive behavior improved student comfort

Text-based feedback exposes a mix of keywords such as helpful, clear, interactive alongside concerns like fast or boring, reflecting varied pacing preferences.

Sentiment analysis leans majority positive, with a minority of negative tones linked mostly to presentation speed and engagement gaps.

In summary, students appreciate the quality of content and instructor clarity, but expect:

Slightly slower delivery

More engagement-focused sessions

Enhanced presentation style for better retention

Overall, the course successfully delivers value, with clear opportunities to further refine the learning experience.
